y weapon spec high, and have never gained anything on my pa cap from increasing it.  Perhaps it is something with the difference between sword spec and thrust, or possibly only makes a difference at lower weapon spec.  I've always been at at least 3/4 spec so wouldn't know how lower spec would effect it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umaoudeib.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maoudeib</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/17/02 3:45:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=200.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 50 thrust skill</span><hr size=1> From what I gather, raising the primary weapon skills does not raise the cap.  However, it does raise the minimum damage, thus increasing the average perf artery.<br><br>So, I suspect 50+ primary weapon skill continues to raise the minimum damage on CS attacks.  However, that is difficult to prove.  As a side benefit your primary weapon style attacks would directly benefit, increasing their cap AND minimum damage.<br><br>However, does the damage per hit use the stated dps of a weapon, or the effective dps?  If your CS skill sets a max perf regardless of the weapon...then a variety of weapons would likely hit that cap, regardless of the specific quality.  But I don't think that is the case.. based on the perfs reported in the high 700's from infiltrators.<br><br>My current weapon: shimmering arcanium guarded rapier.<br><br>16.4/3.5:  16.4 damage/sec  3.5 secs/1 hit = 57.4 damage (units?) per hit.<br><br>Compare to arcanium gladius.<br><br>16.1/3.7  = 59.57 damage (units?) per hit, better than my weapon.<br><br>I'd have to test this out myself, I only noticed this after someone mentioned the gladius would be the superior perf wea